// Arena + heap box (M3). `heap.new` allocates inside the `arena {}` region; the
// whole arena is freed in bulk when the block ends. `box<T>` is the anchor Move type:
// binding it to a new name moves the box (the old name is consumed). `.get()` copies
// the scalar back out, so the result outlives the arena.
fn main() -> i32 {
  r: i32 := arena {
    p: box<i32> := heap.new(42)
    q: box<i32> := p
    q.get()
  }
  return r
}
